WEBVTT

1
00:00:31.533 --> 00:00:32.783
<i>We get back to base camp.</i>

2
00:00:32.784 --> 00:00:35.829
<i>I still gotta write up
this geo field report for Site 42.</i>

3
00:00:36.580 --> 00:00:39.582
<i>You're gonna update the
techniques and methods sheet too. right?</i>

4
00:00:39.583 --> 00:00:41.792
<i>Yeah. Yeah. I'll make sure to include it.</i>

5
00:00:41.793 --> 00:00:44.193
<i>File the report
once you get back to Happy Valley.</i>

6
00:00:44.754 --> 00:00:45.881
<i>And cross-check the...</i>

7
00:00:47.132 --> 00:00:48.632
<i>Hey. do you see that over there?</i>

8
00:00:48.633 --> 00:00:49.884
<i>Where?</i>

9
00:00:49.885 --> 00:00:51.093
<i>Ten o'clock.</i>

10
00:00:51.094 --> 00:00:52.344
<i>What is that?</i>

11
00:00:52.345 --> 00:00:54.764
<i>I don't know.
I'm gonna go check it out.</i>

12
00:02:17.389 --> 00:02:21.309
PROTECT THE LEADER
AT ALL COSTS

13
00:05:25.785 --> 00:05:29.705
Taylor. I gotta go monitor
the ionizer cooldown sequence.

14
00:05:29.706 --> 00:05:32.208
Keep an eye out for anything unusual.

15
00:05:33.084 --> 00:05:34.502
Aye. aye. sir.

16
00:05:38.882 --> 00:05:41.050
Happy Valley. <i>Ranger-2</i>.

17
00:05:41.051 --> 00:05:43.553
Ion engine deactivation is complete.

18
00:05:44.137 --> 00:05:47.014
<i>All argon fuel injectors
have been rerouted to the plasma drive</i>

19
00:05:47.015 --> 00:05:48.183
<i>for the final burn</i>.

20
00:05:49.267 --> 00:05:50.644
<i>Copy.</i> Ranger-2.

21
00:05:51.353 --> 00:05:52.896
<i>Deactivation confirmed.</i>

22
00:05:53.855 --> 00:05:55.273
<i>Any issues with the changeover?</i>

23
00:05:55.774 --> 00:05:57.776
<i>Negative. All systems nominal.</i>

24
00:05:58.652 --> 00:05:59.652
Good.

25
00:05:59.653 --> 00:06:01.737
After we authenticate
the final command sequence

26
00:06:01.738 --> 00:06:03.239
for the slingshot from Houston.

27
00:06:03.240 --> 00:06:05.908
we will remotely initiate
the final Earth burn.

28
00:06:05.909 --> 00:06:07.869
<i>Copy that.</i> Ranger-2 out.

29
00:06:13.166 --> 00:06:15.668
<i>Commander Poole. I have
the final fuel consumption estimates...</i>

30
00:07:06.386 --> 00:07:07.470
Message from Dev.

31
00:07:10.307 --> 00:07:13.309
All right. They're checking
the final plasma drive start-up numbers.

32
00:07:13.310 --> 00:07:14.768
We gotta keep everything on track.

33
00:07:14.769 --> 00:07:17.062
Make sure to mirror
that last diagnostic upload to <i>Ranger</i>.

34
00:07:17.063 --> 00:07:18.648
Copy. Transmitting.

35
00:07:19.149 --> 00:07:21.192
Looks like <i>Ranger-2</i>'s on target.

36
00:07:21.776 --> 00:07:23.653
Two hours. four minutes till final burn.

37
00:07:24.404 --> 00:07:26.615
Good. All right. I'll be right back.

38
00:07:33.788 --> 00:07:34.789
How's he doing?

39
00:07:35.373 --> 00:07:37.291
I think I must take him to medical bay.

40
00:07:37.292 --> 00:07:40.045
No way. He saw our faces.

41
00:07:40.545 --> 00:07:42.171
When he wakes up in there.
we're gonna be fucked.

42
00:07:42.172 --> 00:07:43.840
If we keep him here. he could die.

43
00:07:45.717 --> 00:07:47.635
Yeah. I don't think we have a choice.

44
00:07:47.636 --> 00:07:49.345
Easy for you to say. Ed.

45
00:07:49.346 --> 00:07:52.474
You're not the one who's gonna go to jail
when he picks you out of a lineup.

46
00:07:55.727 --> 00:07:57.062
I take him.

47
00:07:57.646 --> 00:07:58.647
All right?

48
00:07:59.648 --> 00:08:01.024
Decision final.

49
00:08:03.360 --> 00:08:05.070
What are you gonna say to the doc?

50
00:08:07.280 --> 00:08:08.990
Accident with cargo loader.

51
00:08:10.325 --> 00:08:12.117
Okay. That's good.

52
00:08:12.118 --> 00:08:13.702
And when he wakes up?

53
00:08:15.830 --> 00:08:18.123
We have to cross that bridge
when we get to it.

54
00:08:18.124 --> 00:08:19.792
I'm sure Dima will help out.

55
00:08:19.793 --> 00:08:21.086
He has before.

56
00:08:30.011 --> 00:08:31.596
It will be fine.

57
00:08:34.224 --> 00:08:35.642
I hope so.

58
00:08:47.571 --> 00:08:49.154
We're running out of time. Dale.

59
00:08:49.155 --> 00:08:52.199
Tell us who else is involved
and you are free to go.

60
00:08:52.200 --> 00:08:54.202
Like I told you before.
I don't know anything.

61
00:08:55.161 --> 00:08:56.829
Just let me go.

62
00:08:56.830 --> 00:08:59.624
Please. you gotta stop this.

63
00:09:03.336 --> 00:09:04.503
What you doing?

64
00:09:04.504 --> 00:09:06.214
Increasing CO2 levels in room.

65
00:09:09.050 --> 00:09:11.720
You ever have
carbon dioxide poisoning before. Miles?

66
00:09:13.264 --> 00:09:16.015
Very quickly
it will become hard to breathe.

67
00:09:16.016 --> 00:09:18.226
Your heart rate will increase.

68
00:09:19.936 --> 00:09:22.396
Your head will feel like
it's gonna explode.

69
00:09:22.397 --> 00:09:24.106
And soon. you'll wish it had.

70
00:09:24.107 --> 00:09:25.025
Please don't do this.

71
00:09:25.026 --> 00:09:27.860
Give us the names of those involved.

72
00:09:27.861 --> 00:09:29.778
and we'll stop this right now.

73
00:09:29.779 --> 00:09:31.740
I told you. I don't know anything.

74
00:09:54.387 --> 00:09:57.848
You should start feeling
the effects of the CO2 quite soon.

75
00:09:57.849 --> 00:09:59.475
Please don't do this.

76
00:10:07.025 --> 00:10:08.818
Who were you working with?

77
00:10:10.946 --> 00:10:14.032
Tell us what you know
and we'll stop this.

78
00:10:14.783 --> 00:10:17.035
I don't know anything. I swear.

79
00:10:39.266 --> 00:10:40.641
Where are they?

80
00:10:40.642 --> 00:10:42.810
Please.

81
00:10:42.811 --> 00:10:45.729
Please.
I'm gonna be sick.

82
00:10:45.730 --> 00:10:47.983
Just tell us where they are.

83
00:10:54.197 --> 00:10:55.573
You got some on my shoe!

84
00:11:01.037 --> 00:11:03.163
Please.

85
00:11:03.164 --> 00:11:04.790
I don't know anything. Please.

86
00:11:04.791 --> 00:11:07.543
This isn't working.
and we're running out of time.

87
00:11:07.544 --> 00:11:09.921
We gotta try something else.

88
00:11:10.589 --> 00:11:12.673
Please. Please let me go.

89
00:11:15.552 --> 00:11:17.512
Please. man. I just wanna see my family.

90
00:11:18.305 --> 00:11:19.848
Just let me see my family.

91
00:11:28.148 --> 00:11:29.608
Please.

92
00:11:57.052 --> 00:11:58.553
Miss Madison?

93
00:12:11.691 --> 00:12:12.817
Come in.

94
00:12:14.694 --> 00:12:15.695
Good morning.

95
00:12:16.863 --> 00:12:18.239
Yes?

96
00:12:18.240 --> 00:12:19.406
Sorry.

97
00:12:19.407 --> 00:12:22.117
Eli was wondering
if you'd be able to come to his office.

98
00:12:25.038 --> 00:12:27.332
- Can't it wait?
- He says it's important.

99
00:12:39.594 --> 00:12:41.053
I'm feeling pretty confident

100
00:12:41.054 --> 00:12:43.931
that the security on Happy Valley
has it in hand.

101
00:12:43.932 --> 00:12:47.977
as your people well know.
because my people detected them attempt...

102
00:12:49.062 --> 00:12:51.481
Margo. thank you for coming by.

103
00:12:55.151 --> 00:12:56.486
Hello. Margo.

104
00:13:02.742 --> 00:13:04.119
Director Morozova.

105
00:13:04.703 --> 00:13:05.829
I...

106
00:13:06.329 --> 00:13:08.665
I wish I'd known
you were coming.

107
00:13:09.249 --> 00:13:10.332
I would have prepared.

108
00:13:10.333 --> 00:13:13.086
No preparations are necessary.

109
00:13:13.753 --> 00:13:15.713
A nice surprise. isn't it?

110
00:13:15.714 --> 00:13:16.840
Yes.

111
00:13:17.841 --> 00:13:18.967
Yes. it is.

112
00:13:19.551 --> 00:13:22.636
Feels like she and I talk
pretty much every day lately

113
00:13:22.637 --> 00:13:24.096
over this damn thing.

114
00:13:24.097 --> 00:13:27.600
But I haven't seen Irina in person
since Leningrad.

115
00:13:27.601 --> 00:13:30.978
We had the best dinner
at that place.

116
00:13:30.979 --> 00:13:34.064
They served that little fried fish
with the mashed potatoes...

117
00:13:34.065 --> 00:13:35.608
- Koryushka.
- Koryushka.

118
00:13:35.609 --> 00:13:38.569
Honestly. I haven't been able
to stop thinking about it.

119
00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:42.489
Well. I've come to observe
the culmination of our efforts

120
00:13:42.490 --> 00:13:44.325
to bring the asteroid to Earth.

121
00:13:44.326 --> 00:13:46.493
It's gonna be
a special moment for all of us.

122
00:13:47.455 --> 00:13:49.663
Eli tells me you have
settled right back in.

123
00:13:49.664 --> 00:13:53.334
Kinda hard to settle in
when you're followed everywhere you go.

124
00:13:53.335 --> 00:13:54.961
I can imagine.

125
00:13:55.545 --> 00:13:57.839
Well. you don't have to
endure it much longer.

126
00:13:58.548 --> 00:14:01.967
After asteroid has been put on
a correct trajectory for Earth.

127
00:14:01.968 --> 00:14:05.222
you and I are returning to Star City.

128
00:14:07.140 --> 00:14:08.266
Wonderful.

129
00:14:35.001 --> 00:14:35.835
Great.

130
00:14:35.836 --> 00:14:38.754
We need to make sure we don't miss
any contributors to comm latency.

131
00:14:38.755 --> 00:14:41.215
We've run 50 end-to-end tests.
Results match predictions.

132
00:14:41.216 --> 00:14:43.343
Make sure
we get those test reports back ASAP.

133
00:14:43.927 --> 00:14:45.387
- Excuse me.
- Yes. sir.

134
00:14:55.522 --> 00:14:56.523
What's going on?

135
00:14:57.274 --> 00:14:59.609
Irina Morozova is here.

136
00:15:00.944 --> 00:15:02.153
In Houston?

137
00:15:02.654 --> 00:15:05.364
She was supposed to be in Moscow
with Korzhenko when the burn happens.

138
00:15:05.365 --> 00:15:07.575
You know. maybe it's about
this sabotage rumor.

139
00:15:07.576 --> 00:15:11.078
Whatever it is. we need to get
word to our mutual acquaintance.

140
00:15:11.079 --> 00:15:12.359
Have you been in touch with him?

141
00:15:13.081 --> 00:15:15.541
I sent him the latest
kinetic impact calculations this morning.

142
00:15:15.542 --> 00:15:16.917
but I haven't heard back.

143
00:15:16.918 --> 00:15:18.295
He's not answering his phone.

144
00:15:18.795 --> 00:15:20.588
You may need to go to him in person.

145
00:15:20.589 --> 00:15:22.756
We're less than two hours away to burn.

146
00:15:22.757 --> 00:15:24.174
- I can't...
- Aleida. please.

147
00:15:24.175 --> 00:15:25.759
I'll cover for you while you're gone.

148
00:15:25.760 --> 00:15:28.889
I'd go myself.
but I've got a lot of eyes on me.

149
00:15:30.140 --> 00:15:31.141
Okay.

150
00:15:32.642 --> 00:15:35.604
Tell him he needs to leave Houston.
It's not safe for him here anymore.

151
00:15:37.439 --> 00:15:38.564
He's not gonna listen.

152
00:15:38.565 --> 00:15:39.566
Make him.

153
00:15:42.152 --> 00:15:43.361
Please.

154
00:16:00.420 --> 00:16:01.421
Commander.

155
00:16:05.175 --> 00:16:06.884
Any update on Miles Dale?

156
00:16:06.885 --> 00:16:08.093
He's not talking yet.

157
00:16:08.094 --> 00:16:10.430
But I think
we should be making progress soon.

158
00:16:11.056 --> 00:16:12.223
Keep questioning him.

159
00:16:12.224 --> 00:16:14.476
My gut says
that he's involved in this somehow.

160
00:16:15.143 --> 00:16:17.478
And any news about
the missing equipment downstairs?

161
00:16:17.479 --> 00:16:21.065
No. ma'am. Just a lot of people pissed off
at being searched repeatedly.

162
00:16:23.109 --> 00:16:25.152
I want everyone
who doesn't have a mission-essential job

163
00:16:25.153 --> 00:16:27.112
to be confined to their quarters
until this is all over.

164
00:16:27.113 --> 00:16:28.864
And continue the sweep of the base.

165
00:16:28.865 --> 00:16:31.033
If someone really is planning
something against <i>Ranger</i>.

166
00:16:31.034 --> 00:16:32.826
we need to figure it out fast.

167
00:16:32.827 --> 00:16:33.954
Yes. ma'am.

168
00:16:37.415 --> 00:16:40.793
Team two. start mods at nine through 15.

169
00:16:40.794 --> 00:16:43.505
Team three. mods 16 through 22.

170
00:16:46.049 --> 00:16:47.466
Team one. you're with me.

171
00:16:47.467 --> 00:16:48.385
What's going on?

172
00:16:48.386 --> 00:16:50.135
You all need to return
to your quarters immediately.

173
00:16:50.136 --> 00:16:52.179
- Why?
- Orders of base commander.

174
00:16:52.180 --> 00:16:53.098
Mandatory curfew.

175
00:16:53.099 --> 00:16:55.308
All non-essential personnel
are restricted to quarters.

176
00:16:55.892 --> 00:16:56.893
Bullshit.

177
00:16:57.394 --> 00:16:58.936
Take him.

178
00:16:58.937 --> 00:17:01.021
- Let's go.
- Get your hands off of me.

179
00:17:14.995 --> 00:17:18.707
<i>Return to your quarters
immediately if you are not...</i>

180
00:17:20.583 --> 00:17:23.920
<i>Non-essential workers are to stay
in lockdown for the next 36 hours.</i>

181
00:17:25.796 --> 00:17:27.590
<i>Return to your quarters immediately.</i>

182
00:17:27.591 --> 00:17:30.844
<i>I repeat. non-essential workers.
stay in your rooms.</i>

183
00:18:13.094 --> 00:18:14.470
Check-in's at 4:00.

184
00:18:14.471 --> 00:18:15.804
I'm... I'm not here for a room.

185
00:18:15.805 --> 00:18:21.269
Do you know which room Sergei.
Bezukhov is in?

186
00:18:22.062 --> 00:18:23.563
That was so sad.

187
00:18:25.398 --> 00:18:26.732
What was sad?

188
00:18:26.733 --> 00:18:30.236
Wha... He stayed here for a few weeks.

189
00:18:30.237 --> 00:18:32.863
I figured he was here
for some sort of business thing.

190
00:18:32.864 --> 00:18:35.367
Yeah. we do get businessmen
every once in a while.

191
00:18:36.576 --> 00:18:40.664
He was from Yugoslavia. I think.
or maybe it was Sweden.

192
00:18:41.331 --> 00:18:44.876
And yesterday he just...
ups and shoots himself.

193
00:18:49.714 --> 00:18:51.132
He shot himself?

194
00:18:51.925 --> 00:18:53.260
It's such a shame.

195
00:18:53.843 --> 00:18:58.097
He was just a...
Seemed like a real sweet guy.

196
00:18:58.098 --> 00:18:59.891
Always had a smile.

197
00:20:07.709 --> 00:20:08.710
Water?

198
00:20:18.929 --> 00:20:21.723
You were just down here
hiding among us this whole time?

199
00:20:23.308 --> 00:20:25.310
We all have things to hide. no?

200
00:20:26.519 --> 00:20:27.728
Mr. Black Market.

201
00:20:44.537 --> 00:20:46.289
My friend was very helpful.

202
00:20:51.419 --> 00:20:52.629
Hey. buddy.

203
00:20:53.547 --> 00:20:54.839
How you holding up?

204
00:20:59.719 --> 00:21:01.929
Please. man. you gotta believe me.

205
00:21:01.930 --> 00:21:03.974
I don't know what it is you want to know.

206
00:21:06.059 --> 00:21:07.602
God. I want to believe you.

207
00:21:08.270 --> 00:21:09.478
I really do.

208
00:21:09.479 --> 00:21:12.106
That you're just an upstanding individual

209
00:21:12.107 --> 00:21:14.943
caught in the middle
of an unfortunate situation.

210
00:21:28.915 --> 00:21:30.207
Amanda?

211
00:21:30.208 --> 00:21:31.543
Yeah.

212
00:21:33.795 --> 00:21:34.880
What is this?

213
00:21:36.965 --> 00:21:40.594
We know all about
your little import-export business.

214
00:21:41.428 --> 00:21:45.265
Which makes your lovely little wife
an accessory.

215
00:21:49.352 --> 00:21:50.437
Accessory?

216
00:21:50.979 --> 00:21:52.856
She's looking at five years.

217
00:21:54.274 --> 00:21:56.192
Felony. theft. and distribution.

218
00:21:57.235 --> 00:21:59.153
- Son of a bitch.
- And your kids.

219
00:21:59.154 --> 00:22:00.529
Hey. you stay away from my kids.

220
00:22:00.530 --> 00:22:02.782
No. don't worry about them.
They'll be fine.

221
00:22:03.491 --> 00:22:05.659
Child Protective Services
will take good care of them.

222
00:22:05.660 --> 00:22:07.995
Hey. you...
Hey. come here. you motherfucker!

223
00:22:07.996 --> 00:22:09.955
Hey! Fuck! Fuck!

224
00:22:11.791 --> 00:22:13.251
No. please. man.

225
00:22:14.169 --> 00:22:15.502
Please. man. not my family.

226
00:22:15.503 --> 00:22:16.922
Please don't do that.

227
00:22:17.505 --> 00:22:19.507
Don't do that.

228
00:22:20.008 --> 00:22:21.468
No. please. please.

229
00:22:22.010 --> 00:22:23.260
Please. not my family. Please.

230
00:22:23.261 --> 00:22:25.679
I didn't do this to your family. Miles.

231
00:22:27.140 --> 00:22:28.225
You did.

232
00:22:29.476 --> 00:22:30.769
No. no. no.

233
00:22:31.603 --> 00:22:33.396
You want your family safe.

234
00:22:34.105 --> 00:22:35.356
So do we.

235
00:22:35.357 --> 00:22:37.107
Help me out here.

236
00:22:37.108 --> 00:22:38.651
Fuck me.

237
00:22:38.652 --> 00:22:40.111
I can't. I just...

238
00:22:42.656 --> 00:22:45.909
You tell us what we need to know.
we'll keep them safe.

239
00:22:55.126 --> 00:22:56.710
You'll all be safe.

240
00:22:56.711 --> 00:22:58.421
If you help me out.

241
00:23:11.142 --> 00:23:12.644
Okay.

242
00:23:13.436 --> 00:23:15.021
Okay.

243
00:23:17.857 --> 00:23:18.942
They're...

244
00:23:22.737 --> 00:23:24.405
They're on sub-level four.

245
00:23:24.406 --> 00:23:27.325
Fuck. Fuck. Fuck.

246
00:23:30.120 --> 00:23:31.288
Motherfucker.

247
00:23:34.332 --> 00:23:35.625
Fuck.

248
00:23:41.798 --> 00:23:44.925
<i>Auto-sequences are now executing step 785.</i>

249
00:23:44.926 --> 00:23:46.928
<i>Happy Valley to</i> Ranger.

250
00:23:50.724 --> 00:23:53.517
When we get down there
I want every inch searched.

251
00:23:58.648 --> 00:24:00.566
Missions check.

252
00:24:00.567 --> 00:24:02.735
No. don't worry about it now.
Pick it up and go.

253
00:24:02.736 --> 00:24:04.528
Wait until Scott's out of here...

254
00:24:04.529 --> 00:24:05.614
Whoa.

255
00:24:06.114 --> 00:24:08.157
How did they even access sub-level four?

256
00:24:08.158 --> 00:24:09.867
I thought we sealed off the lower floors.

257
00:24:09.868 --> 00:24:12.162
Someone circumvented the lockout.

258
00:24:13.580 --> 00:24:15.080
Let's go.

259
00:24:15.081 --> 00:24:17.374
Get extra rounds.
