<i>- Lee? Let me talk to Ed.</i>

514
00:42:53.033 --> 00:42:54.242
<i>I know he's in there with you.</i>

515
00:42:56.369 --> 00:43:00.039
- He j... not here.
<i>- Don't start with me.</i>

516
00:43:00.040 --> 00:43:01.917
<i>Not after all we've been through.</i>

517
00:43:06.213 --> 00:43:07.254
Hi. Bob.

518
00:43:07.255 --> 00:43:08.881
What the hell are you doing?

519
00:43:08.882 --> 00:43:10.174
<i>Well. Dani...</i>

520
00:43:10.175 --> 00:43:13.594
- Ed. this is crazy. You gotta stop this.
- Why?

521
00:43:13.595 --> 00:43:17.057
So you can haul this thing back to Earth
and let Mars wither up and die?

522
00:43:17.682 --> 00:43:19.934
- No. thank you.
- <i>This ain't about Mars.</i>

523
00:43:19.935 --> 00:43:22.519
<i>This is about changing things
for the better on Earth.</i>

524
00:43:22.520 --> 00:43:24.188
<i>Mars is not our home. Ed.</i>

525
00:43:24.189 --> 00:43:25.941
That's where you're wrong. Dani.

526
00:43:26.650 --> 00:43:28.026
My family's here.

527
00:43:29.194 --> 00:43:30.779
My future's here.

528
00:43:35.242 --> 00:43:37.160
See. that's the difference
between you and me.

529
00:43:38.203 --> 00:43:40.663
You're still tied
to that blue little planet.

530
00:43:40.664 --> 00:43:43.332
<i>Of course. I am. We all are.</i>

531
00:43:43.333 --> 00:43:45.835
<i>That is what matters. That is our home.</i>

532
00:43:47.087 --> 00:43:48.588
Not anymore.

533
00:44:19.578 --> 00:44:22.455
Words have no wings
but they can fly a thousand miles.

534
00:44:25.333 --> 00:44:27.294
This is my home.

535
00:44:29.421 --> 00:44:31.006
Mine too.

536
00:44:34.801 --> 00:44:36.594
<i>If those engines burn.</i>

537
00:44:36.595 --> 00:44:39.346
<i>even for a few seconds longer
past our 20-minute window.</i>

538
00:44:39.347 --> 00:44:41.307
<i>the asteroid won't turn for Earth.</i>

539
00:44:41.308 --> 00:44:42.641
<i>Palmer. get suited up.</i>

540
00:44:42.642 --> 00:44:44.226
<i>I need you to put a stop to this.</i>

541
00:44:44.227 --> 00:44:46.562
They're trying to lock us out
of our own ship?

542
00:44:46.563 --> 00:44:49.940
Well. technically they're engaging
a diagnostic and checkout engine protocol.

543
00:44:49.941 --> 00:44:51.859
but... Yeah. Same idea.

544
00:44:51.860 --> 00:44:54.403
I don't care what we have to do.
We must stop them.

545
00:44:54.404 --> 00:44:57.282
If they override the flight computer.
there is nothing <i>Ranger</i> can do.

546
00:45:00.410 --> 00:45:02.120
They go around us. We go around them.

547
00:45:03.830 --> 00:45:05.122
What do you mean?

548
00:45:05.123 --> 00:45:09.501
We upload a shutdown command that.
bypasses the safeguards

549
00:45:09.502 --> 00:45:13.589
of the nuclear fusion reactor controls
and turn off the engines.

550
00:45:13.590 --> 00:45:14.924
Right at the end of the Earth burn.

551
00:45:14.925 --> 00:45:16.175
I don't understand.

552
00:45:16.176 --> 00:45:18.552
They can't burn to Mars
if they don't have the gas.

553
00:45:18.553 --> 00:45:21.055
<i>Ranger</i>'s flight deck doesn't
have authorization to execute that.

554
00:45:21.056 --> 00:45:22.348
but we can do it from here.

555
00:45:22.349 --> 00:45:23.724
And if we send up code

556
00:45:23.725 --> 00:45:26.685
that commands <i>Ranger</i>'s reactors
to stop powering the engines.

557
00:45:26.686 --> 00:45:28.103
they'll be forced to shut down.

558
00:45:28.104 --> 00:45:30.231
With the communication lag.

559
00:45:30.232 --> 00:45:32.984
any command we send
would take five minutes to get to <i>Ranger</i>.

560
00:45:33.485 --> 00:45:34.903
Then we should get started.

561
00:45:37.280 --> 00:45:38.490
All right.

562
00:45:39.115 --> 00:45:40.450
This has to work. I mean...

563
00:46:05.225 --> 00:46:06.434
Margo?

564
00:46:15.485 --> 00:46:17.279
Wernher and I used to sit up here.

565
00:46:18.280 --> 00:46:20.323
We'd have lunch every few days.

566
00:46:21.491 --> 00:46:23.076
He'd tell me what I was doing right.

567
00:46:24.244 --> 00:46:26.538
He'd tell me
what I was doing wrong.

568
00:46:27.372 --> 00:46:28.999
Try to give me advice.

569
00:46:30.417 --> 00:46:32.627
Usually just listen to me complain.

570
00:46:36.298 --> 00:46:37.841
I was standing right there.

571
00:46:40.176 --> 00:46:41.386
Where you are now.

572
00:46:42.095 --> 00:46:45.265
After everything came out
about what he did during the war.

573
00:46:48.268 --> 00:46:49.895
I asked him if he knew.

574
00:46:51.479 --> 00:46:52.814
About the camps.

575
00:46:53.398 --> 00:46:54.733
The deaths.

576
00:46:55.525 --> 00:46:57.444
I'll never forget what he said.

577
00:46:59.404 --> 00:47:01.364
"Progress is never free.

578
00:47:02.866 --> 00:47:06.202
There is always a cost."

579
00:47:09.915 --> 00:47:11.207
You're not him.

580
00:47:12.626 --> 00:47:13.627
No.

581
00:47:15.545 --> 00:47:17.547
But maybe a part of me is.

582
00:47:24.846 --> 00:47:27.182
Margo. we really need your help in there.

583
00:47:28.934 --> 00:47:31.186
This is not a place for feelings.

584
00:47:33.438 --> 00:47:35.106
Just the facts.

585
00:47:38.443 --> 00:47:43.365
Wernher made it seem like...
he had no choice.

586
00:47:44.991 --> 00:47:47.285
But there is always a choice.

587
00:47:48.453 --> 00:47:49.704
Just like you said.

588
00:47:55.210 --> 00:47:59.047
That asteroid comes to Earth.
then the Mars program is dead.

589
00:48:00.006 --> 00:48:01.715
Just like Sergei said.

590
00:48:01.716 --> 00:48:04.719
Maybe not this year. but soon.

591
00:48:08.223 --> 00:48:11.643
People up there.
they don't care about Mars.

592
00:48:12.477 --> 00:48:14.980
- They just care about themselves.
- Maybe.

593
00:48:16.606 --> 00:48:22.069
But if they succeed. then NASA. Roscosmos.
and the M-7 have no choice

594
00:48:22.070 --> 00:48:25.699
but to continue investing in Happy Valley

595
00:48:27.492 --> 00:48:29.578
and the future of the space program.

596
00:48:31.204 --> 00:48:34.457
We can't let them throw away
everything we've built.

597
00:48:42.382 --> 00:48:44.217
Are you saying what I think you're saying?

598
00:48:46.386 --> 00:48:48.305
"Progress is never free."

599
00:49:07.198 --> 00:49:08.324
<i>Sam. what's your status?</i>

600
00:49:08.325 --> 00:49:11.828
<i>Okay.
I'm finishing securing the tether.</i>

601
00:49:16.458 --> 00:49:17.458
<i>Okay.</i>

602
00:49:19.461 --> 00:49:23.214
<i>Override handle has been secured
in the up position.</i>

603
00:49:23.215 --> 00:49:25.799
Okay. now there should be
an electrical connector labeled

604
00:49:25.800 --> 00:49:29.595
<i>J-13 EXT RF to the port side
of the override switch.</i>

605
00:49:29.596 --> 00:49:32.890
<i>That's where you can connect the P13
connector coming off your transceiver.</i>

606
00:49:32.891 --> 00:49:34.851
<i>- Do you see that. Sam?
- Copy.</i>

607
00:49:41.358 --> 00:49:45.069
<i>Okay. You should be able to receive
engine telemetry now.</i>

608
00:49:45.070 --> 00:49:46.112
Signal confirmed.

609
00:49:46.821 --> 00:49:49.323
As soon as I input the timing
for the <i>Mars burn</i>. you have to keep

610
00:49:49.324 --> 00:49:52.034
<i>the override switch handle
in the up position</i>

611
00:49:52.035 --> 00:49:54.453
<i>for the entire duration of the burn.</i>

612
00:49:54.454 --> 00:49:55.956
<i>Copy that.</i>

613
00:50:14.349 --> 00:50:17.935
If we were able to insert this code
directly into what MOCR's uplinking.

614
00:50:17.936 --> 00:50:20.521
it might be able to prevent
their shutdown command

615
00:50:20.522 --> 00:50:22.774
from stopping the Mars orbit capture burn.

616
00:50:23.817 --> 00:50:27.237
But how are we going to modify it
if they're still writing it?

617
00:50:27.946 --> 00:50:29.698
I'll input it right before uplink.

618
00:50:35.912 --> 00:50:36.912
Let's do it.

619
00:50:43.879 --> 00:50:45.046
But I'm gonna input the code.

620
00:50:46.256 --> 00:50:51.845
- Aleida. No. Absolutely not.
- There are too many eyes on you.

621
00:50:54.055 --> 00:50:55.265
It has to be me.

622
00:50:56.308 --> 00:50:57.809
Or it will never work.

623
00:51:05.775 --> 00:51:08.445
<i>Override is still engaged. Holding steady.</i>

624
00:51:10.614 --> 00:51:13.616
<i>Okay. Don't let the unit
touch the hull plate.</i>

625
00:51:13.617 --> 00:51:15.910
<i>An ion charge could fry the circuits.</i>

626
00:51:15.911 --> 00:51:16.995
<i>Copy.</i>

627
00:51:33.011 --> 00:51:34.054
Sam. are you there?

628
00:51:35.388 --> 00:51:36.389
Come in. Sam.

629
00:51:36.932 --> 00:51:38.475
<i>I've got company.</i>

630
00:51:39.559 --> 00:51:40.810
<i>It's Palmer.</i>

631
00:51:49.945 --> 00:51:51.987
The reactor shutdown path
is almost done compiling.

632
00:51:51.988 --> 00:51:54.615
Gotta send the command in the next 60
seconds if it's gonna get there in time.

633
00:51:54.616 --> 00:51:56.785
I'm typing as fast as I can.

634
00:52:18.431 --> 00:52:19.432
Okay. Done.

635
00:52:20.976 --> 00:52:21.977
Uplink complete.

636
00:53:06.605 --> 00:53:08.857
Come on. Come on. Come on. Palmer.

637
00:53:16.948 --> 00:53:18.388
<i>No!</i>

638
00:53:21.745 --> 00:53:23.747
Sam? Sam!

639
00:53:24.789 --> 00:53:28.877
<i>The override switch
is locked in the up position.</i>

640
00:53:29.377 --> 00:53:32.963
<i>Looks like
she used her tether to secure it.</i>

641
00:53:32.964 --> 00:53:35.758
<i>The goddamn carabiner's jammed closed.</i>

642
00:53:35.759 --> 00:53:37.719
<i>Gonna have to try and cut through it.</i>

643
00:53:38.220 --> 00:53:39.345
<i>Okay. Do it fast.</i>

644
00:53:39.346 --> 00:53:40.972
<i>We have less than a minute.</i>

645
00:54:02.702 --> 00:54:04.621
Come on. Come on.

646
00:54:08.667 --> 00:54:10.834
<i>I'm almost through.</i>

647
00:54:10.835 --> 00:54:13.296
<i>Hurry. Palmer!
You've got 12 seconds.</i>

648
00:54:14.339 --> 00:54:15.799
<i>One last tether.</i>

649
00:54:23.390 --> 00:54:25.683
Ranger.
<i>Engine shutdown for Earth burn.</i>

650
00:54:25.684 --> 00:54:26.976
<i>In five.</i>

651
00:54:26.977 --> 00:54:28.060
Four.

652
00:54:28.061 --> 00:54:29.104
<i>Three.</i>

653
00:54:29.813 --> 00:54:32.399
- Two.
<i>- One.</i>

654
00:55:30.081 --> 00:55:33.042
<i>Happy Valley</i>.
Ranger<i>. We have negative engine shutdown.</i>

655
00:55:33.043 --> 00:55:36.128
I say again.
we have negative engine shutdown.

656
00:55:36.129 --> 00:55:38.631
Wow!

657
00:55:38.632 --> 00:55:40.591
Son of a bitch.

658
00:55:40.592 --> 00:55:42.302
Yeah!

659
00:56:09.829 --> 00:56:12.832
Commander. the asteroid
is on track to enter Mars' orbit.

660
00:56:14.376 --> 00:56:16.419
- Commander?
- I heard you.

661
00:56:16.962 --> 00:56:18.338
I just need a minute.

662
00:56:36.231 --> 00:56:37.440
What happened?

663
00:56:38.441 --> 00:56:40.110
Why didn't it work?

664
00:56:42.445 --> 00:56:44.446
The engines are still on.

665
00:56:44.447 --> 00:56:45.532
I don't know.

666
00:56:46.157 --> 00:56:47.575
The calculations were right.

667
00:56:47.576 --> 00:56:51.036
And the code was successfully
inserted into the uplink packet.

668
00:56:51.037 --> 00:56:52.706
Something's off here.

669
00:56:53.373 --> 00:56:55.291
The-The shutdown reactor command was sent.

670
00:56:55.292 --> 00:56:59.588
but it was immediately
superseded by a restart command?

671
00:57:01.172 --> 00:57:02.756
Someone messed with this code.

672
00:57:02.757 --> 00:57:07.846
I even checked to make sure we haven't
missed any contributors to comm latency.

673
00:57:10.223 --> 00:57:11.266
You did this.

674
00:57:15.562 --> 00:57:17.230
You.

675
00:57:19.566 --> 00:57:21.942
What? That's absurd.

676
00:57:21.943 --> 00:57:25.112
Seth was still encoding while I
was writing the command sequence.

677
00:57:25.113 --> 00:57:28.532
And besides. you don't have
the expertise required to know...

678
00:57:28.533 --> 00:57:32.202
Perhaps not.
but I can tell when someone is lying.

679
00:57:32.203 --> 00:57:33.830
As you are now.

680
00:57:38.043 --> 00:57:39.544
Take her into custody.

681
00:57:40.128 --> 00:57:44.173
- Right now. She has deceived...
- Irina. that is a serious accusation.

682
00:57:44.174 --> 00:57:46.550
She and Ayesa have
always had their own agenda.

683
00:57:46.551 --> 00:57:47.969
Aleida.

684
00:57:49.095 --> 00:57:50.680
That's not true. is it?

685
00:57:51.598 --> 00:57:54.643
You di... Did you do this?

686
00:57:55.560 --> 00:57:59.564
- No. No. I didn't.
- It wasn't her.

687
00:58:02.108 --> 00:58:05.153
I inserted the reactor restart command.

688
00:58:06.613 --> 00:58:08.281
Aleida had nothing to do with it.

689
00:58:15.914 --> 00:58:17.040
No.

690
00:58:19.960 --> 00:58:20.960
Not you.

691
00:58:23.380 --> 00:58:25.465
You shouldn't have done that. Margo.

692
00:58:29.302 --> 00:58:31.429
There will be consequences.

693
00:58:32.764 --> 00:58:33.765
I know.

694
00:58:47.779 --> 00:58:49.697
<i>In a brazen act.
an unknown group</i>

695
00:58:49.698 --> 00:58:56.328
has taken control of asteroid 2003LC.
More widely known as Goldilocks.

696
00:58:56.329 --> 00:59:00.165
In light of this action.
the asteroid is no longer headed to Earth

697
00:59:00.166 --> 00:59:02.459
but has in fact gone into Mars' orbit.

698
00:59:02.460 --> 00:59:04.628
<i>News of the asteroid's hijacking</i>

699
00:59:04.629 --> 00:59:06.630
<i>has reverberated around the world</i>

700
00:59:06.631 --> 00:59:09.633
<i>with calls from both presidents
Gore and Korzhenko</i>

701
00:59:09.634 --> 00:59:14.680
<i>to convene an emergency meeting of the M-7
as well as the UN Security Council.</i>

702
00:59:14.681 --> 00:59:15.640
<i>A rare sign of unity...</i>

703
00:59:15.641 --> 00:59:17.933
<i>Authorities say
it is still unclear</i>

704
00:59:17.934 --> 00:59:19.768
<i>who exactly is behind the hijacking.</i>

705
00:59:19.769 --> 00:59:24.648
NASA administrator Eli Hobson
has vowed that anyone found to be involved

706
00:59:24.649 --> 00:59:28.361
will be prosecuted
to the fullest extent of the law.

707
00:59:33.783 --> 00:59:36.369
Stop.
We're stationed over there.

708
00:59:40.916 --> 00:59:42.834
Pack them two by two in the corner.

709
00:59:46.463 --> 00:59:47.756
I'll be right back.

710
00:59:49.549 --> 00:59:51.383
- Make sure...
- Guess it's automatic.

711
00:59:51.384 --> 00:59:54.145
- All right. All right.
- This goes in the breech.

712
01:00:02.020 --> 01:00:03.270
Bishop. what is this?

713
01:00:03.271 --> 01:00:04.711
We got the green light from Houston.

714
01:00:06.274 --> 01:00:07.442
To go into North Korea?

715
01:00:08.026 --> 01:00:09.069
Affirmative.

716
01:00:12.656 --> 01:00:14.990
Isn't this all a little excessive?
It's over.

717
01:00:14.991 --> 01:00:16.951
We don't know what we're walking into.

718
01:00:16.952 --> 01:00:18.578
And I have orders.

719
01:00:22.582 --> 01:00:23.874
I was not told about any of this.

720
01:00:23.875 --> 01:00:25.918
- Things are moving fast. ma'am.
- That may be.

721
01:00:25.919 --> 01:00:29.463
But the last time I checked I am
still the commander of this base.

722
01:00:29.464 --> 01:00:32.592
So unless the word comes from me.
there will be no raid.

723
01:00:33.927 --> 01:00:39.266
Due respect. my orders come directly from
the DOD and they supersede your command.

724
01:00:41.601 --> 01:00:42.601
Let's move out!

725
01:00:43.270 --> 01:00:44.687
- Here we go!
- Let's go!

726
01:00:44.688 --> 01:00:46.022
Okay. Let's move.

727
01:01:01.830 --> 01:01:03.372
Who else is in your crew?

728
01:01:06.001 --> 01:01:08.295
Who are you working with?

729
01:01:11.631 --> 01:01:13.924
Ch...

730
01:01:18.013 --> 01:01:19.973
What the fuck?

731
01:01:22.642 --> 01:01:23.642
God.

732
01:01:24.811 --> 01:01:26.855
Are you okay?

733
01:01:29.649 --> 01:01:32.276
Come on. Let's get out of here.
Let's go.

734
01:01:40.452 --> 01:01:42.453
<i>Guns in place.
Preparing to breach.</i>

735
01:01:42.454 --> 01:01:44.623
<i>Assessing the situation out. We'll advise.</i>

736
01:01:45.123 --> 01:01:46.707
<i>Try that one.</i>

737
01:01:46.708 --> 01:01:47.792
They are here.

738
01:01:48.293 --> 01:01:49.294
Shit.

739
01:01:52.881 --> 01:01:54.674
- Miles. are you okay?
- Yeah.

740
01:01:56.593 --> 01:01:58.178
Do you hear what's happening?

741
01:01:58.720 --> 01:01:59.720
What?

742
01:01:59.721 --> 01:02:02.056
They're about to attack
the North Korean quarters.

743
01:02:02.057 --> 01:02:04.643
Ed. Sparks. Rich.
they're all in there right now.

744
01:02:09.314 --> 01:02:11.024
We gotta do something.

745
01:02:12.234 --> 01:02:13.754
- I'm tired of this shit.
- Yeah.

746
01:02:14.319 --> 01:02:17.112
It's time we remind them
who really runs this base. Right?

747
01:02:17.113 --> 01:02:18.073
Yeah!

748
01:02:18.074 --> 01:02:19.573
- Let's do it!
- Let's do it!

749
01:02:19.574 --> 01:02:21.700
- Who's with me?
- Yeah!

750
01:02:27.249 --> 01:02:28.375
Here. Go ahead.

751
01:02:29.668 --> 01:02:30.793
Open that door.

752
01:02:30.794 --> 01:02:32.087
That's it.

753
01:02:33.338 --> 01:02:35.256
Sir!
The Americans. they are coming in!

754
01:02:35.257 --> 01:02:36.382
Keep them out!

755
01:02:36.383 --> 01:02:37.883
We must protect our territory!

756
01:02:37.884 --> 01:02:39.261
Yes sir! Let's go!

757
01:02:52.983 --> 01:02:54.823
<i>Confirm...</i>

758
01:02:56.611 --> 01:02:57.612
<i>Clear!</i>

759
01:03:00.031 --> 01:03:01.782
Fire in the hole!

760
01:03:04.536 --> 01:03:05.536
Stay here.

761
01:03:06.454 --> 01:03:07.913
Three. Two. One.

762
01:03:07.914 --> 01:03:09.665
Three. Two. One.

763
01:03:09.666 --> 01:03:11.375
Stop!

764
01:03:15.422 --> 01:03:17.883
Shit!

765
01:03:18.425 --> 01:03:20.093
No!

766
01:03:25.390 --> 01:03:27.434
What the fuck is...

767
01:03:51.124 --> 01:03:52.124
My God...

768
01:04:14.606 --> 01:04:16.398
Hey! All right. Listen.

769
01:04:16.399 --> 01:04:18.318
That's enough! Let her go!

770
01:04:19.194 --> 01:04:20.153
- Stop!
- Jesus!

771
01:04:20.154 --> 01:04:24.740
Hey! Stop! Stop! Stop!

772
01:04:24.741 --> 01:04:25.991
Break this up.

773
01:04:25.992 --> 01:04:27.451
Hey! Stop! Stop.

774
01:04:27.452 --> 01:04:28.577
- Hey!
- Hey!

775
01:04:28.578 --> 01:04:30.163
- Get off of me!
- Break it up!

776
01:04:36.586 --> 01:04:39.004
- Hey! Hey. Hey!
- Break this up!

777
01:04:39.005 --> 01:04:41.423
- It's your fault!
- No! Calm down!

778
01:04:41.424 --> 01:04:44.636
- Hey! Break it up! No. no!
- You have got to break it up!

779
01:05:30.140 --> 01:05:31.224
Dani?

780
01:05:39.733 --> 01:05:40.734
No. no.

781
01:05:41.234 --> 01:05:43.694
No. no. Hey.

782
01:05:43.695 --> 01:05:45.030
No. Hey.

783
01:05:45.822 --> 01:05:47.908
No. No. no.

784
01:05:50.327 --> 01:05:51.827
Hey. Hey.

785
01:05:51.828 --> 01:05:53.121
Help! Come on!

786
01:05:54.372 --> 01:05:56.416
We gotta get her to Dima.
Help me up. Lynn.

787
01:06:00.754 --> 01:06:01.755
Get out of the way.

788
01:06:03.173 --> 01:06:04.257
Clear the way!

789
01:06:08.970 --> 01:06:10.347
Maintain pressure.

790
01:06:11.181 --> 01:06:12.723
Start an IV.

791
01:06:12.724 --> 01:06:14.058
Inserting line now.

792
01:06:14.059 --> 01:06:16.394
I need three liters. normal saline.

793
01:06:17.020 --> 01:06:18.062
Get her on O2.

794
01:06:18.063 --> 01:06:20.147
Hey. Dani. Look at me. Hey.

795
01:06:20.148 --> 01:06:21.399
You're gonna be fine.

796
01:06:21.900 --> 01:06:23.818
Okay? You're gonna be fine.

797
01:06:24.319 --> 01:06:25.654
You got this.

798
01:06:27.697 --> 01:06:29.490
Lungs are wet.

799
01:06:29.491 --> 01:06:31.116
She's aspirating.
And stand by with something.

800
01:06:31.117 --> 01:06:32.618
I need room.

801
01:06:36.331 --> 01:06:39.124
Vitals are failing.
I need to start a central line.

802
01:06:39.125 --> 01:06:40.626
Where is my X-ray?

803
01:06:40.627 --> 01:06:42.378
We need to operate immediately.

804
01:06:46.216 --> 01:06:48.634
Pupils are blown.
Stay with us. Dani.

805
01:06:48.635 --> 01:06:50.845
- Still dropping.
- You hang in there. Dani.

806
01:06:51.513 --> 01:06:52.681
Maintain pressure.

807
01:06:53.723 --> 01:06:55.349
Compress rate increasing.

808
01:06:55.350 --> 01:06:57.393
BP 80 over 40 and falling.

809
01:06:57.394 --> 01:06:59.812
- Pulse 130. IV below...
- Come on.

810
01:07:51.197 --> 01:07:52.990
You can't let them do this.

811
01:07:52.991 --> 01:07:54.117
I don't have a choice.

812
01:07:54.784 --> 01:07:57.203
The Russians withdrew
her diplomatic immunity.

813
01:08:30.779 --> 01:08:32.489
It'll be okay. Aleida.

814
01:09:22.455 --> 01:09:26.793
<i>I've always been captivated
with the idea of justice.</i>

815
01:09:28.003 --> 01:09:31.214
<i>It's what attracted me
to engineering in the first place.</i>

816
01:09:35.093 --> 01:09:36.887
<i>The sense of right and wrong.</i>

817
01:09:38.929 --> 01:09:40.432
<i>That I was in control.</i>

818
01:10:04.748 --> 01:10:06.458
Comrade Morozova.

819
01:10:06.958 --> 01:10:08.126
please come in.

820
01:10:08.710 --> 01:10:10.252
<i>But the truth is</i>

821
01:10:10.253 --> 01:10:13.548
<i>the world is not as simple
as we want it to be.</i>

822
01:10:16.134 --> 01:10:19.346
<i>It can't just be boiled down
into an equation.</i>

823
01:10:23.225 --> 01:10:26.228
<i>Especially when it comes to human beings.</i>

824
01:10:32.234 --> 01:10:38.657
<i>We are flawed.
unpredictable. and full of contradictions.</i>

825
01:10:41.159 --> 01:10:43.244
<i>It's taken me most of my life to realize</i>

826
01:10:43.245 --> 01:10:47.624
<i>it's exactly these traits
that make us so resilient.</i>

827
01:10:49.000 --> 01:10:54.881
<i>That give credence to the
improbable idea that anything is possible.</i>

828
01:10:59.094 --> 01:11:01.513
<i>Even in the darkest of times.</i>

829
01:11:56.568 --> 01:11:59.737
<i>Your Honor. I was always told</i>

830
01:11:59.738 --> 01:12:03.742
<i>that we shouldn't let personal feelings
cloud our search for the truth.</i>

831
01:12:06.411 --> 01:12:08.038
<i>But looking back now.</i>

832
01:12:09.456 --> 01:12:11.166
<i>I don't think that's right.</i>

833
01:12:12.459 --> 01:12:14.502
<i>Our feelings may not be convenient.</i>

834
01:12:17.714 --> 01:12:19.925
<i>They may even slow our progress.</i>

835
01:12:22.510 --> 01:12:26.681
<i>But they are also the only way to truly
begin to understand</i>

836
01:12:27.974 --> 01:12:30.185
<i>the world around us.</i>

837
01:12:32.979 --> 01:12:35.857
<i>And the new worlds that await us.</i>

838
01:12:44.821 --> 01:12:46.821
